Shape style editing
To edit the attributes of facial images via GAN model, Shen _et al_.â€‰ \[ [SYTZ20])\] assumed that for any binary semantics, there may exist a hyperplane in the latent space serving as the separation boundary. This hyperplane in the latent space can be used for editing the image style. We adapted their approach to our SDF-StyleGAN space for 3D shape style editing. We use the shape labels provided in  \[ [MKC18])\] to divide the chair category into two groups: chairs with and without arms. A DGCNN network \[ [WSLâˆ—19])\] was trained to infer whether an input chair contains arms or not. We then randomly generated 10000 chairs using SDF-StyleGAN and divided them into two groups using the trained classification network. As the latent codes of these generate shapes are known, the hyperplane ğ’â‹…ğ’™+d=0â‹…ğ’ğ’™ğ‘‘0\\bm{n}\\cdot\\bm{x}+d=0 that separates these two groups can easily be computed. For any generated shape or a shape obtained by GAN inversion, we can change its latent code ğ’šğ’š\\bm{y} to ğ’šâˆ’Î·â€‹(ğ’â‹…ğ’š+d)â€‹ğ’ğ’šğœ‚â‹…ğ’ğ’šğ‘‘ğ’\\bm{y}-\\eta(\\bm{n}\\cdot\\bm{y}+d)\\bm{n}, Î·â‰¥0ğœ‚0\\eta\\geq 0, to modify the shape style from â€œwithout armsâ€ to â€œwith armsâ€, or vice versa. Similarly on the car category, we use the label â€œwith roofâ€ and â€œwithout roofâ€ to find the separation plane and edit the shape style. In [Fig.12]In 5 Applications â€£ SDF-StyleGAN: Implicit SDF-Based StyleGAN for 3D Shape Generation"), we demonstrate this kind of shape style editing, and we find that the original geometry of the input shapes is also well-preserved.

![Refer to caption]Figure 12: Shape style editing based on the algorithm of \[ [SYTZ20])\]. The style editing on chairs is to add arms, and the style editing on cars is to add car roofs.

Shape interpolationâ€„ A straightforward application is to perform shape interpolation in the ğ’µğ’µ\\mathcal{Z} space, or the ğ’²ğ’²\\mathcal{W} space. [Fig.13]In 5 Applications â€£ SDF-StyleGAN: Implicit SDF-Based StyleGAN for 3D Shape Generation") shows the intermediate results of the interpolation between two chairs, in the ğ’µğ’µ\\mathcal{Z} space. Due to the use of GAN model, each intermediate result is plausible, and the transition of shape geometry between adjacent frames is also smooth.

![Refer to caption]Figure 13: An example of shape interpolation in the ğ’µğ’µ\\mathcal{Z} space.
